  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces, add them to a baking tray and drizzle them with <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong></p>\n<p>Add a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix well</p>\n<p>Put them in the oven for 20-25 min or until they're golden brown and crispy</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>thigh fillets</strong> and season them lightly with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Cook for 3 min or until starting to brown, turning occasionally for even colouring</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong></p>\n<p>Strip the <strong>rosemary</strong> and <strong>thyme</strong> leaves from the stalks and chop finely</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped </strong><strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to the chicken</p>\n<p>Cook for 3 min or until the vegetables have softened slightly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/783.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped </strong><strong>rosemary</strong> and <strong>thyme</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min </p>\n<p>Stir in the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>paste</strong> and cook for 1 min further </p>\n<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
